<sect1 id="RemoveSuffix">
  <title>RemoveSuffix</title>

  <para><emphasis role="bold">STD.Str.RemoveSuffix<indexterm>
      <primary>STD.Str.RemoveSuffix</primary>
    </indexterm><indexterm>
      <primary>Str.RemoveSuffix</primary>
    </indexterm><indexterm>
      <primary>RemoveSuffix</primary>
    </indexterm>(</emphasis> <emphasis>source, suffix</emphasis> <emphasis
  role="bold">)</emphasis></para>

  <informaltable colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
    <tgroup cols="2">
      <colspec colwidth="80.50pt"/>

      <colspec/>

      <tbody>
        <row>
          <entry><emphasis>source</emphasis></entry>

          <entry>A string a ser pesquisada.</entry>
        </row>

        <row>
          <entry><emphasis>suffix</emphasis></entry>

          <entry>O final de string a ser removido.</entry>
        </row>

        <row>
          <entry>Return:<emphasis> </emphasis></entry>

          <entry>RemoveSuffix retorna um valor de string.</entry>
        </row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </informaltable>

  <para>A função <emphasis role="bold">RemoveSuffix</emphasis> retorna a
  string <emphasis>source</emphasis> com o texto do parâmetro
  <emphasis>suffix</emphasis> removido do final dessa string. Se a string
  <emphasis>source</emphasis> não terminar com <emphasis>suffix</emphasis>, a
  string <emphasis>source</emphasis> será retornada sem alterações.</para>

  <para>Exemplo:</para>

  <programlisting format="linespecific">IMPORT STD;
STD.STr.RemoveSuffix('a word away','away');   //returns 'a word'
STD.STr.RemoveSuffix('a word a way','away');  //returns 'a word a way'
</programlisting>
</sect1>
